						<p><hi rend="bold">Trailōkya[malla-Mallidēva-Mahārājā] Śaka 1061, Siddhārthin = 1139 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Much damaged. Seems to refer to the contents of the inscription No. 316 of 1905. Consecration of the god Kēśavadēva on the southern side of the Rudrapāda temple and a grant of land at Vallūru by a <hi rend="italic">Pradhāni</hi> officer of the king.</p>						

